body:
This adds functions, descriptions, and does a small amount of reordering and rewording.  I tried to cleanly separate the changes into four commits (rewording, reordering, adding descriptions, adding commands) to make it easier to review.

This follows on from #1734 which I find hard to review given all the formatting changes making it hard to see what precisely has changed.  It does not end up in the same place as that PR, it is basically my alternative to it.

@kehiy @fiatjaf

A simple way to do Kanban Boards because https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/pull/1665 is too complex.
I intend to implement this in GitPlaza soonish but I hope I can get some feedback first.

